text:
I was thrilled about the opening of a new store in the neighborhood and couldn't wait to give it a try. Unfortunately, my first visit was marred by the presence of a grumpy and impatient auntie.

Not only did her attitude dampen my excitement, but the meesiam I ordered turned out to be mediocre and overly sweet for my taste. Nevertheless, I reminded myself that I am not obliged to support someone who provides unfriendly service.

Don't even have any price list and break down of separate items eg: egg and so on or halal muis cert..price of food can change according to different people who serve...1 day food can cost $4 tomorrow $5...everyday buy same food and can suka suka give different price..if sit down and eat their price different..like that also can serve
Too spicy!! Most spicy nasi Padang I ever eaten.
Really delicious sotong hitam, whole sotong instead of rings
